editorialSummary.text: Relaxed neighborhood eatery serving Japanese favorites like sushi rolls, sashimi & tempura.

originalText.text: Because I was staying at the Hilton Garden / Midtown, I walked across the street and saw this place. They have outdoor seating on the street but interior was warm and inviting. They have a large sushi bar and a nice private dining area where you can take off your shoes and dine in privacy, perfect for a work or family occasion. Because I was dining alone I preferred to eat in a table in the back and felt comfortable. The menu was decent but not a traditional Japanese restaurant but I did enjoy the Black Cod Misozaki (fish marinated in miso and lightly grilled, it was very delicate and the chef prepared a beautiful garnish of avocado and ikura / salmon roe.) it wasnâ€™t enough for dinner so I also ordered two pieces of Ikura and Uni (sea urchin) with a glass of Pinot Grigio - I decided not to order miso soup or riceâ€¦ that costs extra. The total bill was $76. Including tax. Granted that the seafood flew from California, like meâ€¦ and I wondered why the heck was I ordering sushi when I could get it back in CA! ðŸ¥´ Anyway, dinner was fine, the wasabi wasnâ€™t real it was the squirt kind, no edamame was offered, no hot towels for the hands, no orange sherbet or tangerine for dessert, and the sad thing was that it wasnâ€™t plated aesthetically (w/o garnish, at these prices?) I felt the service could have been more hospitable too. Also they locked the doors so I had to be let out because there were three rough looking guys tripping out right next to the door entrance. I guess the manager didnâ€™t care about my personal safety as he quickly locked the door behind me! ðŸ¥´ I wonâ€™t come again.

originalText.text: Very nice and fresh sashimi, chirashi was excellent. Service was adequate. Not much of atmosphere. Very expensive though! It is rarely when I can see rainbow or dragon rolls for $45... Still no regrets, would like to be back.

originalText.text:
Been here twice and the food is consistently great. The fish tastes so fresh and high quality. It doesn't taste overly gamey or rubbery. The Salmon Tartare appetizer was my favorite! Love the way it's wrapped in thin avocado slices vs. thick chunks. The Lobster roll is my go to and the size of each piece / meat quantity is excellent. It's a bit pricey, but definitely worth it.

The outdoor dining area is nicely decorated with a bit of a vibe (eg Japanese style sliding doors). The vibe inside is even better.

originalText.text:
First time here.

No mention on the menu of:

Nigiri serving is one not two pieces.
Not served on sushi rice but on dry brown rice.
Items not available on the "Sushi Available Today" menu. They couldn't have sold out as the place is empty on a Friday night.
Not Japanese owned and run. Too many typos on the menu.
Rushed service. Why. The place isn't busy, I'm sure you're not needing my plates to get them back out. Let me try to enjoy my meal in peace.

There are better choices in the area. Keep looking.

Last time here.
